      <h1>Is Renters Insurance Worth It? Cost vs Benefits Explained</h1>
      <p class="article-intro">About 45 percent of U.S. renters have no renters insurance, according to industry surveys — yet 95 percent of homeowners carry homeowners insurance. The gap exists largely because renters assume their landlord's policy protects them, or they underestimate the value of what they own. The reality: renters insurance is one of the most affordable and overlooked financial safety nets available, typically costing less than a Netflix subscription while protecting tens of thousands of dollars in belongings and shielding you from liability claims that could cost far more.</p>
    </header>

    <AdUnit slot="blog-top" format="horizontal" />

